clinical_study.brief_title: A Prospective, Open Label Study Evaluating JUVÉDERM® VOLBELLA With Lidocaine Treatment for the Correction of Skin Depressions in the Infra-orbital Area

brief_summary.textblock: A prospective, open label, study evaluating JUVÉDERM® VOLBELLA with lidocaine treatment for the correction of skin depressions in the infra-orbital area (under the eyes)

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Subjects With a ≥1 Grade Improvement From Baseline in Infra-Orbital Area on the Allergan Infra-Orbital Rating Scale (AIRS) on the Right and Left Side
primary_outcome.description: The Investigator evaluated the severity of skin crease and volume loss in the infra-orbital area on both the right and left sides on the 6-point AIRS ranging from 0 (least severe) to 5 (most severe).

secondary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Subjects With a ≥1 Grade Improvement From Baseline in Infra-Orbital Area on the AIRS on the Right and Left Side
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Baseline, Day 0, Day 14, Month 6, Momth 9, Month 12
secondary_outcome.description: The Investigator evaluated the severity of skin crease and volume loss in the infra-orbital area on both the right and left sides on the 6-point AIRS ranging from 0 (least severe) to 5 (most severe).

secondary_outcome.measure: Injector Ease of Use on an 11-Point Scale
secondary_outcome.description: The injectors rated the ease of injection and ease of modeling of the product on an 11-point scale from 0 (extremely difficult) to 10 (extremely easy).

secondary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Subjects Assessed by the Investigator as Very Well Improved or Well Improved on the 5-Point Global Aesthetic Improvement Scale (GAIS)
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Day 0, Day 14, Month 1, Month 6, Month 9, Month 12
secondary_outcome.description: The Investigator evaluated the subjects global aesthetic improvement on right and left sides using the 5-point GAIS (1=Very Well Improved, 2=Well Improved, 3=Improved, 4=Not Improved, 5=Worsened State). The percentage of subjects assessed as Very Well Improved and Well Improved are reported.

secondary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Subjects Assessed by the Subjects as Very Well Improved or Well Improved on the 5-Point Global Aesthetic Improvement Scale (GAIS)
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Day 0, Day 14, Month 1, Month 6, Month 9, Month 12
secondary_outcome.description: The subjects evaluated their global aesthetic improvement on the right and left sides using the 5-point GAIS (1=Very Well Improved, 2=Well Improved, 3=Improved, 4=Not Improved, 5=Worsened State). The percentage of subjects assessed as Very Well Improved and Well Improved are reported.

secondary_outcome.measure: Subject Overall Eye Appearance Total Score on the 5-Point Periorbital Aesthetic Appearance Questionnaire (PAAQ)
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Day 0, Day 14, Month 1, Month 6, Month 9, Month 12
secondary_outcome.description: Subjects assessed their overall eye appearance on the PAAQ. The PAAQ includes 9 questions about how the subject's overall eye appearance affected them over the past 7 days. Each question is assessed on a 5-point scale from 0 (never/best) to 4 (all of the time/worse), with the total score ranging from 0 (best) to 36 (worse).

arm_group.description: Infra-orbital skin depressions injected with VOLBELLA® with lidocaine.

intervention.description: VOLBELLA® with lidocaine administered to correct skin depression during initial treatment and optional top-up treatment 14 days later.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Has Grade > 0 at screening within each eye (bilateral skin depression in the infra-orbital area), as evaluated by the Evaluating Investigator (EI) using AIRS
- Agree to refrain from undergoing other antiwrinkle/volumizing treatments in the upper two-thirds of the face (eyebrow to cheeks/cheekbones) for the duration of the study
Exclusion Criteria:
- Has undergone cosmetic facial procedures [e.g., face-lift, or other surgeries which may alter the appearance of the infra-orbital area (laser, photomodulation, intense pulsed light, radio frequency, dermabrasion, moderate or greater depth chemical peel, or other ablative procedures), tissue augmentation with dermal fillers or fat injections, or mesotherapy] anywhere in the face, or Vistabel® cosmetic injections in the peri-orbital area, within 6 months prior to entry in the study or be planning to undergo any of these procedures at any time during the study. NOTE: Prior treatment with HA fillers and/or collagen is allowed, provided the treatment was administered more than 12 months prior to study entry
- Has undergone volumizing of the mid face within 12 months prior to study entry
- Has ever received semi-permanent fillers or permanent facial implants (e.g., calcium hydroxylapatite, poly-L-lactic acid, polymethylmethacrylate, silicone, expanded polytetrafluoroethylene) anywhere in the infra-orbital area, or be planning to be implanted with any of these products at any time during the study
- Have a history of skin cancer
- Have a history of hypertrophic scarring
- Have a subcutaneous retaining structure on the face (e.g., meshing, gold strand)

certain_agreements.restrictive_agreement: A disclosure restriction on the PI is that the sponsor can review results communications prior to public release and can embargo communications regarding trial results for a period that is less than or equal to 90 days from the time submitted to the sponsor for review. The sponsor cannot require changes to the communication and cannot extend the embargo.
